subCards.title: India Must Prepare For Violent Future As CDS Chauhan Says Even One Failure Could Prove Catastrophic
subCards.abstract: In a hard-hitting address at the Chanakya Defence Dialogue, CDS General Anil Chauhan warned that global geopolitics is rapidly deteriorating and the world is moving toward an era of intense instability. He said the future will be shaped by faster weapons, robotics, autonomous platforms, massive sensor networks, and multi-domain warfare where cyber, space, and information will be as decisive as land and air. Stressing that “failure in war is catastrophic,” he said India cannot afford complacency as traditional frontlines disappear and entire national infrastructures can now be targeted. With nuclear treaties collapsing and major powers signalling new weapon developments, he warned that the world is entering dangerous territory. He urged India to focus on credible preparedness, cross-domain operations, and strategic technological dominance to secure national interests.

The electric SUV is expected to be priced competitively.
